entry.content:
StylusHandwritingImeCallback is set when web contents are updated, this allowed Direct writing service to request for edit bounds when spen hover over editable fields and blocks navigation icons (back/home/menu) to allow direct writing.



Direct writing service expects onlyRectChanged key along with bundle when only edit field bounds have changed to avoid blocking navigation icons. Issue was happening because this key was not passed with bundle.



Added onlyRectChanged key to bundle when onBoundedEditTextChanged API is called.



This is a reland of commit 2b1ed86013047fdae98768896e3954e832c19327



Original change's description:

> Set StylusHandwritingImeCallback when the web contents is updated

>

> The Stylus Handwriting Toolbar in Chromium was unresponsive when an

> input field was focused without performing any direct writing actions.

> This issue occurred due to the StylusHandwritingImeCallback being set

> only when initiating stylus writing.

>

> Set StylusHandwritingImeCallback when the web contents is updated.

> This ensures that the callback is available even when an input field

> is focused without performing direct writing action.

entry.title: [Promise Icons] Remove promise icons for non-launchable ARC packages
entry.content:
Currently, promise icons are generated when we install non-launchable

ARC packages but they are not deleted when the installation completes.

This is because even though the installation is a success, it never

produces a launchable app to remove the promise icon with.



Hence, this change checks whether the installed ARC package is

launchable and marks the promise app as kCancelled when there is no

installed app to replace it. This will then correctly remove the

promise icon when the package installation completes.

entry.title: Avoid attempts to create an ApkWebAppService when ARC isn't allowed
entry.content:
When ARC isn't allowed for a profile and ApkWebAppService::Get(profile)

is called for the first time, no ApkWebAppService gets created but the

ApkWebAppServiceFactory holds onto the nullptr. After ARC is enabled for

the profile, the ApkWebAppServiceFactory still returns a nullptr when

the ApkWebAppService is requested because we do not attempt to build the

ApkWebAppService again. Hence, this CL ensures we only call/ build the

service when ARC is enabled.

entry.title: Account for document.head() returning null
entry.content:
It is possible for document.head() to return null. Most other call sites

check for this. Add the missing check here. This was causing UBSan

failures in DocumentLoaderTest.



There seem to be a few of these in Blink. Blink likes to use references

when it believes fields are non-null. Tracking non-null pointers is

good, but Blink seems to constantly dereference its nullable pointers

without null checks. The point of categorizing things is to force you to

check for the null on the transition from nullable to non-nullable, but

Blink's coding patterns seem not to do this.

entry.title: HTTPS-First Mode: Count daily navigations and save them in a pref
entry.content:
For the Typically Secure User heuristic, we want to count the number of

entry.title: Increase limit on interest groups per owner from 1000 to 2000.
entry.content:
This is a low-risk increase in the limit on the number of interest

groups per owner from 1000 to 2000. In practice, this limit is rarely if

ever reached. This change has been approved:

ChromeStatus feature: https://chromestatus.com/feature/6751281490427904

I2S: https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/IfmYsMCUoHc/m/yCddTUfgBgAJ



Chrome’s Protected Audience implementation limits the number of IGs that

one IG owner can place the user into. This limit originally served to

limit user device storage resource usage and user device compute

resources during auctions. We found better, more accurate, and less

biased ways to accomplish both of these goals without limiting the

number of IGs that one owner can place the user into, namely switching

to a size limit on all IGs and switching to a timeout on all IGs. This

change simply raises the limit on the number of IGs from 1000 to 2000.

straightforward.

entry.title: Update It2Me host and friends to use a raw access_token
entry.content:
This CL adds a new kAccessToken message field which will be used to

provide a raw access token (i.e. not prefixed with `oauth2:`.

The impetus for this change is that today every caller which calls

into the CRD support host stack via Mojo needs to prefix their

access_token with 'oauth2:' which is error-prone and un-necessary.



Though this would typically be a straight-forward change, there are

two cases that need to be covered for compatibility:

1. The website changes are not in production yet so the It2Me NMH

needs to handle both old and new message fields for now

2. Lacros and Ash can have version skew so some translation is needed

to maintain compatibility.



#1 will be resolved prior to M121 branch point but #2 will require

that the shim code stick around until ~M124. I've added TODOs in the

relevant code blocks to remove the shims when it is safe to do so.



Please note that there are also changes needed in the remote_command

directory however the compat code I've added means that I can split

those out into a separate CL and have them approved by the OWNERs for

that directory.

entry.title: Announce match numbers in find bar results in screen readers.
entry.content:
Previously, when you would run find-in-page (ctrl-F),

on VoiceOver and NVDA the screen reader would announce

the results as you cycle through them ("Result 1 of 4",

"Result 2 of 4", and so on), but JAWS would not (it

was silent, giving no feedback that something happened),

and ChromeVox would not announce anything either (though

I think it reads the text of the match, which the

other screen readers don't do).



This CL fixes the issue with JAWS.



Note that ChromeVox's behavior is completely different (it reads

the full text of the item that matched the search phrase), and

this CL does not change that, which is intentional. It is unclear

if we want to change ChromeVox's behavior.

entry.title: IndexedDB: move some IDBFactory code to IndexedDBBucketContext
entry.content:
The `IndexedDBBucketContext` lifetime is somewhat complicated as

the object manages its own lifetime at times, but is also owned

by the `IndexedDBFactory`. This change is the first in a series

that attempts to simplify bucket context lifetime (creation,

initialization, deletion), which will be necessary in order to

draw clear lines between the bucket sequence and main IDB

sequence.



The specific change in this CL is to move management of the

bucket task queue into `IndexedDBBucketContext`, whereas

previously it was spread across `IndexedDBBucketContext` and

`IndexedDBFactory`. This code is relevant to bucket context

shutdown. There should be no functional change, just better

encapsulation. With this change, it is easier to imagine

`IndexedDBBucketContext` and `IndexedDBFactory` living on separate

threads, however there are also a lot of assumptions about

shutdown synchronicity which this does not resolve.

As part of a large scale refactorization that aims at introducing

ClientSharedImage, this CL refactors several raster buffer providers

to 1. use the new version of DestroySharedImage() (that accepts a

ClientSharedImage parameter instead of a mailbox), and 2. make sure

the ClientSharedImage created by CreateSharedImage() could persist

until the calling of DestroySharedImage().



Bug: 1494911, 1499992

entry.title: Set CC occlusion_immune to true for
entry.content:
kAllowUndamagedNonrootRenderPassToSkip



We fail to update |has_damage_from_contributing_content| when there are

occlusion damages from the other render pass on top. Now set

occlusion_immune to true for kAllowUndamagedNonrootRenderPassToSkip to

avoid the need for re-draw on occlusion damages from top.
